le ways to make the internet work for them. There are already several direct money-making methods for the internet being used today, such as selling used merchandise through sites like Craigslist and eBay.","<strong>How It Works</strong><br/>Below is a step-by-step listing of the gears that make the engine of online credit card processing run. This will give you an excellent introduction to how this service can benefit retailers and anyone who runs or is considering opening up an online merchandising enterprise."]},"id":"d322b999-9461-42a9-b77f-91635d6d0bfd","type":"text"},{"data":{"items":["A customer decides to buy an item listed on your website and they supply their billing details.","The customer s data is transferred to the internet payment gateway with the customer remaining on your site and never directed away to another internet location.","The customer s billing data is then guided through the payment gateway to the online service processor.","From there, the data is passed to the issuing bank, which authenticates the card s validity and ensures that the customer has enough available on the card to make the purchase.","The purchase amount is then set aside by the issuing bank, which sends the processor either an approval or a decline message.","In about 3 to 15 seconds from step 2, the data makes its way back through the gateway to your site, where you have a number of processing options available to you, depending on the type of service you are employing.","Typically the last step is when final payment is securely deposited into your account."],"type":"ol"},"id":"c6391fd1-b9e3-466b-9206-a743553a14f2","type":"list"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["Allowing an online credit card processing service provider to manage all of your credit card transactions made through the internet allows you or your company to bypass the relatively limited site designs and inflexible fee structures of those other online dumping grounds mentioned above, and gives you and your company th